MAMIE:
<i>By the time all of this started happening,</i>

25:28.290 --> 25:33.220
<i>the surrounding area around us</i>
<i>was changing.</i>

25:33.420 --> 25:36.430
<i>And we could see things</i>
<i>that they were doing</i>

25:36.630 --> 25:41.770
<i>with marinas, boat slips, subdivision.</i>

25:41.970 --> 25:45.650
<i>So we knew this was the plan</i>
<i>for our community.</i>

25:45.850 --> 25:50.200
<i>And we knew we had to really stand</i>
<i>to save our community,</i>

25:50.390 --> 25:53.450
<i>because if all of this happened</i>
<i>in our community,</i>

25:53.650 --> 25:56.620
<i>we wouldn't be able to afford</i>
<i>the taxes here,</i>

25:56.820 --> 25:59.250
<i>because we don't have the income</i>

25:59.450 --> 26:03.350
<i>that people from other states</i>
<i>come here with.</i>

26:08.600 --> 26:10.610
(engine starts)

26:21.330 --> 26:23.330
(engine whirring)

26:35.050 --> 26:37.530
MELVIN:
<i>This didn't use to be...</i>

26:37.730 --> 26:40.660
<i>the water didn't use to be</i>
<i>all the way through here.</i>

26:40.860 --> 26:44.620
My mother daddy helped put

26:44.820 --> 26:49.210
<i>the rest of the right-of-way through here</i>
<i>for this water that-that comes by.</i>

26:49.410 --> 26:53.090
That's when--
they call them the intercoastals.

26:53.290 --> 26:57.260
So you could drive, go to Florida,
go all the way around.

26:57.460 --> 26:58.900
<i>Go right on through here.</i>

27:00.990 --> 27:03.990
<i>And now, they got some homes up here.</i>

27:06.040 --> 27:08.940
Oh, you know how long it would take us
to get to Sneads Ferry?

27:09.140 --> 27:11.230
- NATE: <i>About five hours, six hours?</i>
- MELVIN: <i>No, you will...</i>

27:11.430 --> 27:13.820
<i>No, it'd take a whole day.</i>

27:14.020 --> 27:18.410
<i>You could leave Merrimon--</i>
<i>say, 9:00 in the morning</i>

27:18.610 --> 27:21.450
<i>and start from-- back from Silver Dollar,</i>

27:21.650 --> 27:26.420
<i>and it'd be 5:00 'fore we get</i>
<i>to Sneads Ferry that evening.</i>

27:26.620 --> 27:28.710
<i>But you can't shrimp up there in the day.</i>

27:28.910 --> 27:32.100
<i>I mean you can't shrimp at nights,</i>
<i>only days.</i>

27:36.320 --> 27:38.680
See, down east, when I was shrimping
down there last year,

27:38.880 --> 27:40.680
- you could only shrimp at night.
- Yeah, at night.

27:40.880 --> 27:42.930
- And all through the day it's just fish.
- Yeah.

27:43.130 --> 27:45.310
<i>Just fish, and you won't catch</i>
<i>no shrimps at day.</i>

27:45.510 --> 27:46.810
NATE:
<i>And then you got to work with the moon.</i>

27:47.010 --> 27:48.690
MELVIN:
<i>Yeah, you work when the moon come up.</i>

27:48.890 --> 27:50.290
- NATE: <i>You start shrimping.</i>
- MELVIN: <i>Shrimping.</i>

27:53.630 --> 27:55.670
(crank squealing)

28:00.220 --> 28:02.080
(birds chirping)

28:02.280 --> 28:04.220
(indistinct chatter)

28:08.850 --> 28:10.850
(music playing faintly on speakers)

